1
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:08,467
♫ I want to go to the future ♫

2
00:00:08,467 --> 00:00:12,122
♫  Time bears witness to my quirkiness  ♫

3
00:00:12,122 --> 00:00:18,215
♫ I want to seize the day and put the whole world into my head ♫

4
00:00:18,215 --> 00:00:24,341
♫ I want to go back in time to do all the crazy things I didn't do ♫

5
00:00:24,341 --> 00:00:30,662
♫  Don't say goodbye, don't be in a daze, let my radiant light be bright  ♫

6
00:00:30,662 --> 00:00:35,948
♫ We are always looking forward to the unknown future ♫

7
00:00:35,948 --> 00:00:42,948
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:42,948 --> 00:00:48,272
♫ Every day my heart beats for you ♫

9
00:00:48,272 --> 00:00:49,885
♫ Be your light ♫

10
00:00:49,885 --> 00:00:55,448
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,448 --> 00:01:02,048
♫ Every day the sun shines through the window ♫

12
00:01:02,048 --> 00:01:08,515
♫ With the reflection of you being my incredible highlight ♫

13
00:01:08,515 --> 00:01:11,699
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:11,699 --> 00:01:16,120
Thank you for earlier.
[22 Leisure Beer House]

15
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:18,898
Let's not thank each other back and forth.

16
00:01:20,340 --> 00:01:23,559
By the way, keep an eye on that little man.

17
00:01:23,559 --> 00:01:25,566
Don't let him run away again.

18
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:28,344
I'm leaving.

19
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,646
Dawei,

20
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,587
well...

21
00:01:33,587 --> 00:01:35,020
You...

22
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:36,946
By the way,

23
00:01:36,946 --> 00:01:39,340
don't tell your dad about me.

24
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:42,879
I don't want him to meddle in my business.

25
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,954
I'm leaving.

26
00:01:46,954 --> 00:01:48,139
Bye.

27
00:01:48,139 --> 00:01:49,679
Bye.

28
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:57,520
It's such a pity for him to start working so soon.

29
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:59,139
Exactly.

30
00:01:59,139 --> 00:02:02,999
He doesn't even have a degree. How can he find a nice job?

31
00:02:02,999 --> 00:02:04,699
Let's go talk to him.

32
00:02:04,699 --> 00:02:06,119
Sure.

33
00:02:07,159 --> 00:02:08,000
No, we can't.

34
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:08,980
What's wrong?

35
00:02:08,980 --> 00:02:11,839
It won't be effective if we go talk to him.

36
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,960
We have to tell Mr. Gao.

37
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,599
That won't do.

38
00:02:15,599 --> 00:02:17,039
We already promised Dawei.

39
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,908
We can't break our promise.

40
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:22,155
What should we do, then?

41
00:02:31,719 --> 00:02:33,159
I know.

42
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:36,520
We won't tell Gao Bin about it directly.

43
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:38,799
We can just let him find out on his own.

44
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:51,573
Set the balls!

45
00:02:51,573 --> 00:02:53,094
Coming.

46
00:02:54,402 --> 00:02:57,402
[Episode 23: Stubbornly Becoming Who You Are]

47
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,706
You're home?

48
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,376
Dad.

49
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,955
You're not in bed yet?

50
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,412
Not yet.

51
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:32,680
I earned this recently.

52
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,039
I'll put it in your room.

53
00:03:34,039 --> 00:03:35,609
Dawei,

54
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:43,280
you can't just do odd jobs every day.

55
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,589
You can't do odd jobs for the rest of your life.

56
00:03:46,939 --> 00:03:48,987
I have my plans.

57
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:56,020
Sure, we don't have a lot of money,

58
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:59,640
but putting you through school for one more year is not a problem.

59
00:04:00,319 --> 00:04:02,037
Why don't you...

60
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:07,700
work harder and put in more effort? Let's try it again.

61
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,319
If you really can't make it next time,

62
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:12,939
we'll accept it, okay?

63
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,960
Don't mention repeating school to me again.

64
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:22,480
How about you ask Mr. Gao and listen to his advice?

65
00:04:23,639 --> 00:04:27,880
If you mention Gao Bin again, I'll move out of the house.

66
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:30,260
You... Look at you.

67
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:45,779
Would this work?

68
00:04:45,779 --> 00:04:47,800
Don't worry. I've already gathered the information.

69
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:51,346
Dawei comes out around this time every day. Be natural.

70
00:04:52,879 --> 00:04:55,020
You two really know how to cause trouble.

71
00:04:55,020 --> 00:04:56,419
Is the breakfast downstairs not delicious?

72
00:04:56,419 --> 00:04:58,079
You insist on coming to Dawei's place for breakfast.

73
00:04:58,079 --> 00:05:00,399
This place is really famous. The food is delicious.

74
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:03,183
Hurry up and eat. I still have to get to school.

75
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:12,120
Wait, Dad. Eat more slowly. Have some jellied bean curd (soybean pudding).

76
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:19,319
You guys have no idea. I'm afraid of being late.

77
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:23,520
Now that Old Jin isn't there, the Vice Principal is abusing his power.

78
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:26,180
He takes roll calls everyday and makes us keep the school in order.

79
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:29,850
If I'm late, he'll certainly make things hard for me.

80
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,920
Forget it, I'm not eating anymore. I'm leaving.

81
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,880
- Wait, I'm not finished yet, Dad.
- Mr. Gao, have another taste of the jellied bean curd.

82
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:38,499
I have to go to school! I'm really running late!

83
00:05:38,499 --> 00:05:40,779
Try this jellied bean curd!

84
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:47,019
So brainless. He's...

85
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,480
Why are you guys here?

86
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,670
What a coincidence. We're here to eat breakfast.

87
00:05:53,670 --> 00:05:54,500
Have you eaten yet?

88
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,120
Why am I always running into you?

89
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,160
I'm leaving.

90
00:05:57,160 --> 00:06:00,365
Going to work? Keep it up!

91
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,454
Oh my goodness. What are you doing? Who are you trying to scare?

92
00:06:10,454 --> 00:06:12,116
I'm here.

93
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:14,920
You're five minutes late.

94
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:19,100
I... I had a flat tire. I ran all the way here. I just came...

95
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:22,080
Don't make excuses with me. I'm not Principal Jin.

96
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,659
Don't try that with me.

97
00:06:23,659 --> 00:06:28,460
I can see that. Every superior has their own style.

98
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:32,940
Bin, there are no outsiders here.

99
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:34,480
I want to speak my mind with you.

100
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,519
Okay, okay.

101
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:39,719
For the past few years, you've severely underperformed in terms of class hours. Did you know that?

102
00:06:39,719 --> 00:06:41,520
What are you doing?

103
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:43,960
They deducted my salary for that already.

104
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:47,328
Why don't you hold yourself to a higher standard?

105
00:06:47,328 --> 00:06:49,680
Vice Principal, I'm working hard to catch up now.

106
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:53,200
My workload in one year on the track and field team equals that of the past three years.

107
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:56,288
Oh my goodness. If you didn't mention it, I would have forgotten.

108
00:06:56,288 --> 00:06:59,575
About the track and field team, where's your training plan?

109
00:06:59,575 --> 00:07:01,108
That...

110
00:07:01,519 --> 00:07:05,640
In my office. That... There's still a bit I'm not done with yet.

111
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:08,703
Bin, just last year alone,

112
00:07:08,703 --> 00:07:12,366
your self-summary, annual assessment, training plans, and lesson plans,

113
00:07:12,366 --> 00:07:15,179
they're all a mess! Did you know that?

114
00:07:15,179 --> 00:07:18,119
Tell me exactly what are you trying to do.

115
00:07:18,119 --> 00:07:20,659
I belong to the practical group.

116
00:07:20,659 --> 00:07:22,405
You... you what?

117
00:07:22,405 --> 00:07:24,844
Look at your heavy panting! You're a practical person?

118
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:27,279
The disciples take after their masters, you know?

119
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:32,540
Look at you. You... you can't even pass your own physical fitness test, and you still want to coach the track and field team?

120
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,780
What are you doing? Are you falling asleep?

121
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:38,720
I'm... I'm doing self-reflection.

122
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,659
Then go self-reflect somewhere else instead.

123
00:07:40,659 --> 00:07:42,879
Stop torturing me here, okay?

124
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:45,099
Okay, okay.

125
00:07:45,099 --> 00:07:46,599
Wait a minute!

126
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:49,800
If you don't finish the training plans for the track and field team,

127
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,088
you can forget about coaching the team. Do you hear me?

128
00:07:52,088 --> 00:07:54,689
Okay, got it.

129
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:17,700
Is this too obvious?

130
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:20,460
I know him too well. It'll only work like this.

131
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:22,081
Don't worry.

132
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:37,579
One, two, three, four.

133
00:08:37,579 --> 00:08:40,299
Two, two, three, four.

134
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,588
Are you exercising?

135
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,260
Dad, let me tell you something.

136
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:50,080
I'm busy. I don't have time to talk.

137
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:53,879
It's about my future. I'm really confused right now.

138
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:55,559
Can we talk?

139
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:58,240
I'm very confused, too.

140
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,480
Dad, can I just directly get a job

141
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,584
if I don't do well on the college entrance exam?

142
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,079
What's wrong?

143
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,320
What did you say?

144
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,119
I said I want to get a job.

145
00:09:17,119 --> 00:09:18,720
I want to smack you!

146
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,980
Mr. Gao! Mr. Gao! He didn't mean that.

147
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,240
What did he mean then?

148
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,759
I think getting a job is really nice. I'll be free and I can earn money.

149
00:09:23,759 --> 00:09:25,719
- Are you trying to anger me to death?
- Forget it. Forget it.

150
00:09:25,719 --> 00:09:31,139
Dad, think about it. The BBQ restaurant on the next street pays well and the boss is nice.

151
00:09:31,139 --> 00:09:32,140
Why don't you go check it out?

152
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:34,020
Check out what?

153
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:38,960
Gao Yang, I'm telling you,

154
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:41,839
just focus on your studies.

155
00:09:41,839 --> 00:09:44,939
Getting a job isn't what you should consider at your age!

156
00:09:44,939 --> 00:09:46,720
Dad, go check it out.

157
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:49,380
Let go. I'm about to be worked to death.

158
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:53,899
I'll be honest with you, if I don't straighten this out, the three of us will go hungry!

159
00:09:53,899 --> 00:09:54,980
Do you understand?

160
00:09:54,980 --> 00:09:57,279
Why don't you... just take a look?

161
00:09:57,279 --> 00:09:59,640
Exactly. Go take a look.

162
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,980
Let's go.

163
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,477
Leave, leave.

164
00:10:12,279 --> 00:10:16,059
Dad, how about the three of us go play pool?

165
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,804
Get out!

166
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:26,380
Thank goodness I didn't inherit his brain.

167
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:29,415
I already gave him so many hints and he still doesn't understand.

168
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,004
Why don't we take care of it ourselves?

169
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:41,159
- Daddy, I miss you so much!
- Doudou.

170
00:10:41,159 --> 00:10:44,199
Be gentle, be gentle. Your dad is still recovering.

171
00:10:44,199 --> 00:10:45,519
How do you feel today?

172
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:47,263
Not bad.

173
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,200
Is it time for lunch?

174
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,360
- I'll go get it.
- I'll go, I'll go.

175
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,080
I'll go.

176
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:54,359
Be good. Be more gentle.

177
00:10:54,359 --> 00:10:58,440
Look at the way you're peeling that apple. Watch your hands.

178
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:02,679
Doudou, Did Gao Bin treat you badly?

179
00:11:02,679 --> 00:11:06,099
No, he even took me to fill my teeth.

180
00:11:06,099 --> 00:11:07,159
Does it hurt?

181
00:11:07,159 --> 00:11:08,600
No.

182
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:12,180
If I can't even stand that pain, how can I be a man?

183
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:13,087
My goodness.

184
00:11:13,087 --> 00:11:14,296
Doudou.

185
00:11:14,296 --> 00:11:16,519
Doudou grew up too.

186
00:11:16,519 --> 00:11:18,279
Daddy, let me take care of you.

187
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:20,041
Yeah, right.

188
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:21,679
You just talk the talk.

189
00:11:21,679 --> 00:11:24,459
Sister, you've worked hard, too.

190
00:11:24,459 --> 00:11:25,759
Oh, My.

191
00:11:25,759 --> 00:11:29,561
Sis, if no one wants you, I'll raise you.

192
00:11:29,561 --> 00:11:30,919
Why wouldn't anyone want me?

193
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:34,733
Judging by the way you peel an apple, no one would want you.

194
00:11:34,733 --> 00:11:37,226
Jin Doudou, have I been too nice to you?

195
00:11:37,226 --> 00:11:41,373
You're taking advantage of my kindness, you little rascal!

196
00:11:46,279 --> 00:11:50,260
Let's eat dumplings with pork and celery fillings for lunch.

197
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:56,430
[Notice for Missing Person]

198
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:08,230
[Notice for Missing Person]

199
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:10,071
Auntie,

200
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,459
you don't have to publish these anymore.

201
00:12:15,459 --> 00:12:17,624
Why?

202
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:21,479
I don't want to see him.

203
00:12:21,479 --> 00:12:25,260
Wasn't... Wasn't that always your wish?

204
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:31,800
A-Actually, e-ever since I experienced the incident with B-Beibei's dad,

205
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,819
I just thought

206
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,240
I shouldn't ask for too much.

207
00:12:37,979 --> 00:12:40,659
It's good enough to know he's still alive.

208
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,618
Jia'er,

209
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:51,179
I'll find a way to bring your dad home, okay?

210
00:12:51,179 --> 00:12:52,570
N-No need, Auntie.

211
00:12:52,570 --> 00:12:54,552
Y-You really don't need to.

212
00:12:55,299 --> 00:12:57,740
Having you is enough.

213
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:05,059
You've really suffered over the years.

214
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:08,585
No.

215
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:19,840
Wait, I wouldn't dare to eat the meal you guys are paying for.

216
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,294
This is a Hongmen Banquet (trap).

217
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:26,220
Go on. Why were you looking for us?

218
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,140
Let's eat first.

219
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,499
No, no. Let's talk first.

220
00:13:30,499 --> 00:13:31,840
Let's talk as we eat.

221
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:36,379
No, if you don't say your purpose, I won't dare eat this meal.

222
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:42,840
Have you seen Dawei lately?

223
00:13:44,779 --> 00:13:46,539
You two know about it?

224
00:13:46,539 --> 00:13:48,200
Why is Dawei working?

225
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,266
He's not going to school anymore?

226
00:13:50,266 --> 00:13:51,919
I don't know what Dawei is thinking either.

227
00:13:51,919 --> 00:13:55,400
Out of the three of us, he was the most eager one to go to college.

228
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:58,799
He even told us getting a degree is more important than anything else.

229
00:13:58,799 --> 00:14:03,040
Exactly. I didn't pass the exam and didn't want to repeat the year again.

230
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:06,420
Dawei brought me out that night and we talked for a whole night.

231
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:09,479
He told me how nice and how important it is to go to college.

232
00:14:09,479 --> 00:14:13,400
He wanted me to try hard for it again. He just didn't beat me up for it.

233
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,399
He's making you guys repeat school when he's not?

234
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:16,639
Exactly. I don't know either.

235
00:14:16,639 --> 00:14:18,620
That's how it is now.

236
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:20,159
Have you tried to persuade him?

237
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,360
You guys are so close.

238
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,780
How would we dare mention it?

239
00:14:22,780 --> 00:14:25,080
He gets mad every time we mention repeating school.

240
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:27,559
He won't even answer our calls now.

241
00:14:34,242 --> 00:14:39,114
[BBQ]

242
00:14:43,919 --> 00:14:44,759
Forget it.

243
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:47,040
I'll just directly ask him what he's thinking.

244
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:50,399
Even those two can't do anything about it. What can you do?

245
00:14:50,399 --> 00:14:52,884
The school's about to start if we don't handle this now.

246
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:57,004
Dawei doesn't want anyone to meddle in his business.

247
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,126
Let's go, then.

248
00:15:03,059 --> 00:15:04,699
You two again?

249
00:15:04,699 --> 00:15:06,570
Why are you guys always following me?

250
00:15:09,799 --> 00:15:11,797
We're here to eat BBQ kabobs.

251
00:15:11,797 --> 00:15:14,280
I know what you want to say.

252
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:16,559
You're trying to convince me to repeat school, right?

253
00:15:16,559 --> 00:15:20,919
Dawei, we really think it's too early for you to work right now.

254
00:15:20,919 --> 00:15:23,279
You should really consider repeating school again.

255
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:24,759
I don't want to.

256
00:15:24,759 --> 00:15:26,540
Hurry up and scram.

257
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:36,960
What? We're not allowed to eat BBQ kabobs?

258
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:39,920
Let's go. Take a seat. Let's sit here.

259
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,220
Sit down.

260
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:47,025
Hello, Sir, please give us a
menu. We're going to order.

261
00:15:49,179 --> 00:15:51,406
Hurry up.

262
00:15:51,406 --> 00:15:53,719
We're not drinking beer.

263
00:15:55,039 --> 00:15:57,600
Come on, eat!

264
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,159
- Dawei! Dawei!
- Boss! Boss!

265
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:01,000
Boss, he's bullying us!

266
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:01,919
Dawei! Da...

267
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,672
Well,

268
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:28,939
you're working here?

269
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:34,559
Then, what is there to eat here?

270
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,057
Beer,

271
00:16:38,057 --> 00:16:39,639
BBQ kabobs,

272
00:16:39,639 --> 00:16:41,332
peanuts, and soybeans.

273
00:16:41,332 --> 00:16:45,039
What do you do around here?

274
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:49,840
Put meat on a stick, unload, and mop the floor.

275
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,893
What else do you want to know?

276
00:16:56,279 --> 00:16:57,588
Nothing else.

277
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,120
Don't come here again.

278
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,254
Why?

279
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:10,000
No reason.

280
00:17:10,659 --> 00:17:12,685
Don't come to see me anymore.

281
00:17:14,340 --> 00:17:17,759
But... Do you think I want to come looking for you?

282
00:17:17,759 --> 00:17:22,486
I just want to see the result of someone I've tutored before.

283
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,895
You don't have to tutor me ever again.

284
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:37,610
Alright.

285
00:17:39,659 --> 00:17:42,680
You already wrote on this. I don't want it anymore!

286
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:47,304
Why did she leave?

287
00:17:48,839 --> 00:17:50,847
How did the talk go?

288
00:17:50,847 --> 00:17:52,254
Go away!

289
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,572
What are you doing?

290
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:22,479
Are you living here now?

291
00:18:22,479 --> 00:18:23,599
Vice Principal, it's a pleasure to have you here.

292
00:18:23,599 --> 00:18:25,440
How can I help you?

293
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:27,620
Do you know this is the sports equipment room?

294
00:18:27,620 --> 00:18:29,780
Who allowed you...

295
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:32,660
to work here?

296
00:18:34,119 --> 00:18:38,540
Well, that... The office of the PE department is very small.

297
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:43,139
I thought I should leave some room for the young teachers.

298
00:18:43,139 --> 00:18:48,580
Bin, I'm not picking on you because Old Jin is in the hospital.

299
00:18:48,580 --> 00:18:52,660
To put this seriously, this is called private possession of public property, understand?

300
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:55,079
That hat (accusation) is a bit big on me.

301
00:18:55,079 --> 00:18:57,160
All right, all right. Let's not talk about other things.

302
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,940
I'll give you until the end of today to move all your stuff away.

303
00:18:59,940 --> 00:19:02,040
You can't use this place

304
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,139
as your office from now on.

305
00:19:05,139 --> 00:19:08,040
Vice Principal, I've been here for over ten years and you're making me move now?

306
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:11,900
Exactly, no one did anything about you for over ten years.

307
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:15,520
Move out right away and lock the door with this.

308
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,440
Isn't that Mr. Gao?

309
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,499
What are you doing?

310
00:20:02,499 --> 00:20:03,700
Dawei's Dad.

311
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:07,400
Well, the school asked me to remove my personal items.

312
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:10,720
Why? Did you get fired?

313
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:13,160
Which senseless superior fired you?

314
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:16,000
No, no. I just moved to another office.

315
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,260
I knew it. How can they fire such a good teacher like you?

316
00:20:19,279 --> 00:20:24,479
What "good teacher"? They said I'm the worst teacher at school.

317
00:20:24,479 --> 00:20:26,399
You're too humble.

318
00:20:26,399 --> 00:20:28,960
By the way, how's Dawei?

319
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,319
Did he write down his aspirations (college and major)? Where is he going?

320
00:20:31,319 --> 00:20:34,979
Don't mention it. That boy didn't get into any colleges.

321
00:20:34,979 --> 00:20:37,440
Well, repeat school then. Make sure he picks a good class.

322
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,240
I'll help you talk to the teachers.

323
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:42,420
Mr. Gao, don't go through all the trouble. He's working now.

324
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,079
He found a job.

325
00:20:44,079 --> 00:20:46,979
Dawei is only nineteen. How... how can he start working?

326
00:20:46,979 --> 00:20:49,359
That's what I said.

327
00:20:49,359 --> 00:20:51,979
He said he's old enough

328
00:20:51,979 --> 00:20:54,400
and has some kind of plan.

329
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,840
He won't even tell me anything about it.

330
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:01,000
Then do you want me to go and persuade him?

331
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,340
Don't go to talk to him, Mr. Gao.

332
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:05,279
He asked me not to tell you.

333
00:21:05,279 --> 00:21:07,119
I know he respects you,

334
00:21:07,119 --> 00:21:10,340
but you're the one he's most afraid of seeing.

335
00:21:12,419 --> 00:21:16,300
Alright, Dawei's Dad, don't worry about it.

336
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:18,780
I'll find a way to help you.

337
00:21:19,259 --> 00:21:23,959
Mr. Gao, please don't go talk to him. He's keeping everything bottled up inside now.

338
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:26,820
I understand. I'm leaving now.

339
00:21:33,780 --> 00:21:35,359
I can't believe you both.

340
00:21:35,359 --> 00:21:38,429
You just went out to eat and got beer all over yourselves.

341
00:21:38,429 --> 00:21:41,140
You're both underage. You're not allowed to drink alcohol.

342
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:45,823
I really don't know what you kids are thinking about these days.

343
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,480
I ran into Dawei's dad today.

344
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:52,880
He said Dawei isn't planning on repeating school.

345
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:57,039
His dad is so worried. What should we do?

346
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:02,127
Good for you. You finally realized it.

347
00:22:02,127 --> 00:22:03,559
What do you mean?

348
00:22:03,559 --> 00:22:05,100
You guys knew about this a long time ago?

349
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:07,340
Why didn't you tell me?

350
00:22:08,519 --> 00:22:10,680
I gave you so many hints.

351
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:14,820
Well,

352
00:22:14,820 --> 00:22:18,400
did you two get anything out of him?

353
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,479
We got ourselves soaked in beer, didn't we?

354
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,119
Dawei did this?

355
00:22:24,419 --> 00:22:26,739
That won't do. I have to go and ask him.

356
00:22:26,739 --> 00:22:29,720
Mr. Gao, forget it.

357
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,880
He won't say anything when he sees you.

358
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,919
He even despises us.

359
00:22:40,079 --> 00:22:41,618
You're right.

360
00:22:43,039 --> 00:22:45,459
Dawei's dad said the same thing.

361
00:22:45,979 --> 00:22:48,340
Dawei is only nineteen.

362
00:22:48,860 --> 00:22:51,440
What can he do besides repeat school?

363
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,483
What should we do?

364
00:22:59,119 --> 00:23:01,939
Since neither of us can convince him,

365
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:05,540
we can only have her do it.

366
00:23:09,119 --> 00:23:11,940
You're not in the elite class anymore. We're no longer friends.

367
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:13,300
Why did you come to see me?

368
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,459
Who wants to be your friend?

369
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:18,600
We're here to talk about Dawei.

370
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,340
We hope you can talk to him again.

371
00:23:22,380 --> 00:23:25,019
You guys have so much time on your hands. You're in the mood to meddle in someone else's business?

372
00:23:25,019 --> 00:23:28,260
Xiaowen, forget it. Look at her.

373
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:31,942
She won't say anything nice even if she sees Dong Dawei. Hurry up and leave now.

374
00:23:31,942 --> 00:23:36,400
Did you go to visit Dong Dawei yesterday because you care about him?

375
00:23:37,419 --> 00:23:39,739
I care about him?

376
00:23:39,739 --> 00:23:42,060
I just tutored him a few times.

377
00:23:42,060 --> 00:23:44,740
He can do whatever he wants. It's none of my business.

378
00:23:44,740 --> 00:23:48,140
You know he hurt his arm, right?

379
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:51,939
Even if he's not going to school anymore, this job isn't suitable for him.

380
00:23:51,939 --> 00:23:54,100
We're not your friends,

381
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:55,945
but he is, right?

382
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:02,440
See? I told you coming to see her is useless.

383
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:23,740
Sis, please kick the ball to me.

384
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,458
Pay attention to the defense!

385
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:42,139
Go, go!

386
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,957
Watch out, Classmate!

387
00:24:51,019 --> 00:24:54,579
Classmate, don't stand behind the goal. It's dangerous.

388
00:24:54,579 --> 00:24:56,642
Watch the angle of your shot!

389
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,648
Watch out!

390
00:25:16,759 --> 00:25:20,820
I knew that Niu Wanwan wouldn't help us.

391
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:25,199
Blackie. Don't learn from her, Blackie.

392
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:35,580
Hello, who is it?

393
00:25:37,599 --> 00:25:40,220
Who is it? Why aren't you saying anything?

394
00:25:42,359 --> 00:25:44,599
Mom, is that you?

395
00:25:44,599 --> 00:25:47,720
Who's your mom? I'm Niu Wanwan.

396
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:52,759
Why didn't you say anything then? Are you an oddball? What's up?

397
00:25:52,759 --> 00:25:57,860
I'll be at the People's Park at 2 p.m. tomorrow. Go tell Dong Dawei. I'm hanging up.

398
00:25:58,939 --> 00:26:00,079
Who was that?

399
00:26:00,079 --> 00:26:03,880
Niu Wanwan. She said she wants to see Dong Dawei.

400
00:26:12,650 --> 00:26:15,580
Why isn't Dong Dawei here yet?

401
00:26:22,659 --> 00:26:24,279
Did you tell him?

402
00:26:24,279 --> 00:26:27,949
I did. He shoved me and yelled at me.

403
00:26:27,949 --> 00:26:32,840
I'm telling you, this is the last time. I never like to meddle anyway.

404
00:26:36,759 --> 00:26:39,839
Dawei, clean up the table.

405
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,240
Boss, I'm heading out for a while.

406
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,837
Go on.

407
00:27:30,599 --> 00:27:31,519
Where's Wanwan?

408
00:27:31,519 --> 00:27:34,580
Why are you here so late? She already left.

409
00:27:35,140 --> 00:27:38,400
Look at you, you're a man. How can you make her wait so long?

410
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:40,364
Which way did she go?

411
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:43,913
Dawei, ride the bike.

412
00:27:43,913 --> 00:27:45,649
- It'll be faster.
- Okay.

413
00:27:50,839 --> 00:27:52,470
Good luck.

414
00:27:54,599 --> 00:27:58,320
Hurry up! She'll be gone soon!

415
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:00,979
Hurry up, pick up the speed!

416
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:04,320
Xiaowen, Xiaowen, Xiaowen!

417
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:08,580
Do you think if Dawei catches up to her, they will...?

418
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:14,160
I'm more curious about how they met.

419
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,960
You have no idea.

420
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:18,599
Although Dawei is like this now,

421
00:28:18,599 --> 00:28:21,776
he was really something back then. He was Wakabayashi (goalkeeper in Captain Tsubasa) of Tieyuan.

422
00:28:21,776 --> 00:28:26,019
Not just in our No.3 High School, let me tell you, he was a celebrity within the entire city.

423
00:28:26,019 --> 00:28:29,119
It was unquestionable that Niu Wanwan would fall for his charms.

424
00:28:29,119 --> 00:28:32,480
Niu Wanwan... Niu Wanwan likes soccer too?

425
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:34,240
I don't know about that.

426
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,140
I just know that

427
00:28:36,140 --> 00:28:40,160
a man is very charming when he's focused.

428
00:28:41,179 --> 00:28:42,880
- Really?
- Yes.

429
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:44,436
Take me for an example.

430
00:28:47,010 --> 00:28:51,459
Just kidding. Take you as an example. Look, you're really charming when you run too.

431
00:28:51,459 --> 00:28:54,000
A lot of girls would scream for you, right?

432
00:28:54,839 --> 00:28:56,378
Right?

433
00:28:57,759 --> 00:28:59,414
You're shy.

434
00:29:24,079 --> 00:29:25,780
Let's go home. Don't wait anymore.

435
00:29:25,780 --> 00:29:30,240
No, this is the crucial moment of the story. There's going to be a twist.

436
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:31,640
You're treating it as watching a soap opera?

437
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:35,719
No, he still has my bike. What if he doesn't give it back?

438
00:29:35,719 --> 00:29:37,959
Why would he keep your bike?

439
00:29:37,959 --> 00:29:40,319
We'll wait for a while longer.

440
00:29:40,319 --> 00:29:41,559
See? He's back.

441
00:29:41,559 --> 00:29:42,860
How did your talk go?

442
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:44,160
Pretty good.

443
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:48,879
Pretty good? Tell us the details. Did you two...?

444
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:52,119
How is that any of your business?

445
00:29:52,119 --> 00:29:54,539
Take your bike. Thanks.

446
00:29:54,539 --> 00:29:56,316
Dawei,

447
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:59,302
are you sure you're not going back to school?

448
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:06,060
Thank you guys for making so much effort for me recently.

449
00:30:06,060 --> 00:30:08,640
You even invited Wanwan here.

450
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,340
She tried to persuade me too.

451
00:30:10,340 --> 00:30:13,839
But I'm still not going to repeat school.

452
00:30:13,839 --> 00:30:15,920
That's what I told her as well.

453
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:17,622
Why?

454
00:30:18,580 --> 00:30:21,820
I'll show you something. Move over a bit.

455
00:30:26,780 --> 00:30:28,777
A driver's license?

456
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,920
I've already failed twice.

457
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,459
Once in soccer

458
00:30:37,459 --> 00:30:39,439
and once in the college entrance exam.

459
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:42,650
I'm quite talented as a goalie,

460
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,900
but the conditions do not permit it anymore.

461
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:48,240
I'm not good at studying.

462
00:30:48,759 --> 00:30:51,900
I tried and I didn't get a good result.

463
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:57,659
My driving instructor said I'm a pretty good and steady driver.

464
00:30:57,659 --> 00:30:59,580
He said I can be a good driver in the future.

465
00:30:59,580 --> 00:31:02,340
I don't want to lose my third chance.

466
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:06,419
At first, I was pretty bothered by my dad's job.

467
00:31:06,419 --> 00:31:08,559
Now that I think about it,

468
00:31:09,039 --> 00:31:11,499
I'm following in his footsteps.

469
00:31:12,559 --> 00:31:16,319
In a few years, I can drive large vehicles. When the time comes, I'll drive around the world.

470
00:31:16,319 --> 00:31:17,960
It's quite the freedom.

471
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:20,189
That's nice, Dawei.

472
00:31:21,039 --> 00:31:23,820
When I become a big boss in the future,

473
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:26,179
I'll hire you to be my driver.

474
00:31:27,939 --> 00:31:29,409
Gao Yang,

475
00:31:29,820 --> 00:31:32,253
go home and tell your dad that

476
00:31:32,253 --> 00:31:33,820
I...

477
00:31:33,820 --> 00:31:36,742
I won't be doing odd jobs for the rest of my life.

478
00:31:36,742 --> 00:31:38,820
That's my plan.

479
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,419
I haven't told my dad yet.

480
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:44,079
Don't worry.

481
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:47,349
Don't be concerned about me.

482
00:31:47,349 --> 00:31:48,964
I'm leaving.

483
00:31:52,340 --> 00:31:53,895
By the way,

484
00:31:54,499 --> 00:31:56,380
focus on your studies.

485
00:31:56,380 --> 00:31:57,939
Tell me if anyone bullies you.

486
00:31:57,939 --> 00:32:01,180
Who's going to bully us after you leave?

487
00:32:02,759 --> 00:32:03,720
I'm leaving.

488
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,331
- Bye.
- Bye.

489
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:17,080
Everything's here. Please take a look.

490
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:19,016
When I have time.

491
00:32:24,039 --> 00:32:28,240
Well, Vice Principal, why don't you... right now?

492
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,960
I'm busy.

493
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:31,559
Busy with what?

494
00:32:31,559 --> 00:32:32,952
I'm thinking about things.

495
00:32:32,952 --> 00:32:34,723
Thinking about what?

496
00:32:35,900 --> 00:32:38,979
I'm thinking, "why isn't my tea cooling down yet"?

497
00:32:42,739 --> 00:32:44,594
Alright, then.

498
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:47,769
I'll be on my way, then.

499
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:57,117
Xiao Li, you're here to make up for your work, too?

500
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:01,100
Mr. Gao, you're not coaching the track and field team anymore?

501
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:02,799
That's not true.

502
00:33:02,799 --> 00:33:04,960
Then why did the Vice Principal ask me to come talk about coaching the track and field team?

503
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,900
- Xiao Li, are you here?
- Yes.

504
00:33:08,140 --> 00:33:09,300
Come on in.

505
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:11,156
I'm going in there.

506
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:18,440
Xiao Li, the track and field team is the top priority of our school now.

507
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:21,660
It involves our school's pride.

508
00:33:22,254 --> 00:33:24,325
Do you have any ideas?

509
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:56,770
♫ I know the direction of dawn ♫

510
00:33:56,770 --> 00:34:03,935
♫ It's right in front of me, waiting for me to shine ♫

511
00:34:03,935 --> 00:34:10,125
♫  The starlight that shines along the way  ♫

512
00:34:10,125 --> 00:34:16,165
♫ Accompanying me on my adventure, packing my dreams into my heart ♫

513
00:34:16,165 --> 00:34:22,517
♫  I don't fear the rough journey ahead, I will no longer run away  ♫

514
00:34:22,517 --> 00:34:28,357
♫  Maybe I'm not destined for the hardship of this journey  ♫

515
